  "prompt": "If I am talking on whatsapp call to someone and another person calls me on my whatsapp. what status will he get. will it show busy?",
  "response": "When you're on a WhatsApp call with someone and another person tries to call you on WhatsApp, the caller will see one of the following statuses depending on your WhatsApp settings and the platform you're using:\n\n1. **Busy Status**: The caller may see a status indicating that you're \"on another call\" or \"busy\" (e.g., \"Calling...\" with a note like \"Busy on another call\" or \"Line Busy\"). This happens if the app detects that you're already engaged in a call.\n\n2. **Ringing**: If the setting to show your call status as \"busy\" is not enabled or not supported in some cases, the caller might just see the call ringing without any additional status.\n\nThis behavior can also vary slightly depending on whether you're using WhatsApp on Android, iOS, or the desktop app. To ensure consistency, check your WhatsApp settings under **Privacy > Calls** to see if there are options related to call status.\n\nIn summary, the other caller will likely see that you're busy on another call, but the exact message may vary based on your app version and settings.",
